						               													<description>When a group of curious kids snuck into the abandoned Lyeville Cybernautics Academy, they never imagined they'd find so much of the old machinery still in place. Sifting through the detritus, they fixed up the old Robot Club labs where their parents used to spend hours tinkering after school, and founded something new: Robot Fight Club!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a two-player game of fast-paced robot combat. Each game starts with a Scrap Sale, where the players purchase a pair of robots and a selection of upgrades, then a series of Bouts in which they'll duke it out in the hopes of being crowned champion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each of your two robots has its own unique set of Control Cards, and they're shuffled together to create your deck for the game. Each card lets one of your robots do some combination of moving around the arena and attacking the enemy robots. The first player to win two Bouts is declared the champion!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
